6:
Straight ahead lies the entrance to
the Kaleidoscope. Go now, all of you!
That includes you, Vesta!
8:
And abandon you? Have the Guild
Knights lost their mind?!
10:
Far from it! We're Guild Knights, it's
our duty to protect this city!
19:
I sensed an Oudo just now... Who
was that?
21:
That was my father... He descended
into the depths and never returned...
26:
The Oudo of a departed spirit...
Could it be that—
30:
Challua is child of forest. Child of
Spirit Tree!
33:
Hear my voice! Listen to my wish!
Fallen spirits, answer me!
38:
Come together. Hear song... Light
flame...
And go forth!
45:
Incredible... It's like watching a god
at work!
50:
They're giving form and will to the
lingering emotions left in the
Kaleidoscope...
53:
But the spirits aren't being forced by
her hand—as a sorcerer would do...
No, they move entirely of their own
free will!
56: You... are truly a sprite, aren't you?
60: Yes! Challua is sprite of Spirit Tree!
67:
Challua look for friends to save
everybody!
71:
...Someone mind clueing me in to
what's going on?
80:
Y-you mustn't move just yet! Your
wounds are—wait, they're gone!
85:
This is life force manipulation... A
forbidden incantation that controls
life energy itself.
89:
Th-then... it is some form of
necromancy?
93:
It would seem we have the Lord of
the Undead to thank. My goodness,
you certainly align yourself with
some frightening allies.
99:
Necromancy? Th-the Undead? I
think I was better off not knowing
any of that!
103:
Now I finally understand. They're
employing the exact same tactic as
us ancient dragons—reincarnation!
108:
I... see. So, you mean we've got an
immortal army on our side?
112:
Quite the opposite. The Lord of the
Undead has stolen away their ability
to reincarnate.
116:
Right. So we can't expect them to
provide us with endless
reinforcements.
121: I even feel my strength returning...
127:
As do I! I feel like unleashing divine
judgment on the whole lot of them!
132:
Well, I'll be damned... We might just
be able to get things turned around
yet.
137:
Regitare's power... is truly something
else to behold.
147:
Show this thing what you can do,
Schult!
159:
Whoa, what's with all the glum
faces? Our ship hasn't sunk yet. It's
time to bring the fight to them!
163:
You mean... the counterattack has
started?
170:
Oh, Nao! I hear you did some great
work!
175:
Sure did! And I brought a whole
buncha friends with me!
179:
Saw 'em all on the way here! The
people in this town aren't ready to
walk the plank just yet!
184:
And Challua's giving everyone even
more power. We can still keep going!
190:
Seems the winds have shifted—I can
feel them blowing in our favor!
199:
House Felder stands with the
Crimson Blades. We're not out of this
fight yet!
208:
Well, Suizen... What do you have to
say?
212:
Unbelievable... Somehow you all
keep surpassing my expectations. It
beggars belief.
216:
I take back what I said before. We'll
make our stand here! Signal all our
forces!
221:
Well said! Now THAT is the stubborn
brat of a diviner I have always
known!
225: Do you see what I see, Gram?
229:
Now do you understand why I
became Headmistress?
It's for moments like this.
241:
Yumu... I'm in this fight, too. I promise
you—I'm done crying.
244:
That said... Next time I see you,
you're gonna get a nice, hard smack
across the face! Hope you're ready...
